---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Palchat – Bring ideas to life">
  <main class="relative min-h-screen overflow-hidden bg-slate-950 text-slate-50">
    <div class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-0 -z-10">
      <div class="absolute -left-40 top-0 h-80 w-80 rounded-full bg-sky-500/20 blur-3xl sm:-left-32 sm:h-96 sm:w-96" />
      <div class="absolute bottom-0 right-0 h-80 w-80 rounded-full bg-purple-500/20 blur-3xl sm:h-96 sm:w-96" />
      <div class="absolute inset-x-0 top-40 h-64 bg-[radial-gradient(circle_at_top,_rgba(56,189,248,0.18),_transparent_60%)]" />
    </div>

    {/* NAVBAR */}
    <header class="sticky top-0 z-20 border-b border-white/5 bg-slate-950/80 backdrop-blur">
      <div class="mx-auto flex max-w-6xl items-center justify-between px-4 py-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <a href="/" class="flex items-center gap-2">
          <div class="flex h-9 w-9 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-gradient-to-tr from-sky-400 to-purple-500 shadow-lg shadow-sky-500/30">
            <span class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-950">P</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex flex-col">
            <span class="text-base font-semibold tracking-tight">Palchat</span>
            <span class="text-xs text-slate-400">Ideas & tiny tools</span>
          </div>
        </a>

        <nav class="hidden items-center gap-8 text-sm font-medium text-slate-200 md:flex">
          <a href="#hero" class="hover:text-sky-300">Home</a>
          <a href="#features" class="hover:text-sky-300">Why Palchat</a>
          <a href="#workflow" class="hover:text-sky-300">How it works</a>
          <a href="#essay" class="hover:text-sky-300">Ideas</a>
          <a href="/about" class="hover:text-sky-300">About</a>
        </nav>
      </div>
    </header>

    {/* HERO */}
    <section
      id="hero"
      class="mx-auto flex max-w-6xl flex-col gap-10 px-4 py-12 sm:px-6 sm:py-16 lg:flex-row lg:items-center lg:gap-16 lg:py-20 lg:px-8"
    >
      <div class="max-w-xl space-y-6">
        <p class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full border border-sky-500/40 bg-slate-900/80 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-sky-200 shadow-sm">
          <span class="inline-flex h-1.5 w-1.5 rounded-full bg-emerald-400" />
          New · A home for product ideas
        </p>

        <div class="space-y-4">
          <h1 class="text-balance text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl">
            Bring product ideas to life
            <span class="block bg-gradient-to-r from-sky-300 via-cyan-200 to-purple-300 bg-clip-text text-transparent">
              without drowning in tools.
            </span>
          </h1>
          <p class="text-balance text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-300 sm:text-base">
            Palchat is a simple place to collect product ideas and read short essays about building with care. No chat,
            no feed — just clear thinking and tiny tools.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
          <a
            href="#essay"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 rounded-full bg-slate-50 px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-semibold text-slate-950 shadow-lg shadow-slate-900/40 hover:bg-slate-200 focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-sky-400 focus-visible:ring-offset-2 focus-visible:ring-offset-slate-950"
          >
            Read today&apos;s idea
            <span aria-hidden="true">→</span>
          </a>
          <a
            href="#features"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 rounded-full border border-slate-700 bg-slate-900/70 px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-medium text-slate-100 shadow-sm hover:border-sky-400 hover:text-sky-200 focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-sky-500 focus-visible:ring-offset-2 focus-visible:ring-offset-slate-950"
          >
            See how Palchat helps
          </a>
        </div>

        <dl class="grid max-w-md grid-cols-3 gap-4 text-xs text-slate-300 sm:text-sm">
          <div>
            <dt class="font-medium text-slate-100">Format</dt>
            <dd>Short essays & ideas</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt class="font-medium text-slate-100">Tools</dt>
            <dd>Tiny and free</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt class="font-medium text-slate-100">Noise</dt>
            <dd>None</dd>
          </div>
        </dl>
      </div>

      <div class="flex flex-1 items-center justify-center">
        <div class="relative w-full max-w-md">
          <div class="absolute -inset-1 rounded-3xl bg-gradient-to-tr from-sky-500/40 via-cyan-400/20 to-purple-500/40 blur-xl" />
          <div class="relative overflow-hidden rounded-3xl border border-white/10 bg-slate-900/80 p-4 shadow-2xl shadow-sky-900/40 backdrop-blur">
            <p class="mb-2 text-[11px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-sky-300">
              Today&apos;s featured idea
            </p>
            <div class="space-y-3 text-xs text-slate-100 sm:text-sm">
              <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-50 sm:text-base">
                A dependency trap dressed up as efficiency
              </h2>
              <p class="text-slate-300">
                Cheap subscriptions feel like wins on their own. Stack enough of them and you quietly hand off your own
                competence to a row of tools you do not control.
              </p>
              <div class="rounded-2xl bg-slate-800/80 p-3 text-[11px] text-slate-200">
                <p class="font-medium text-amber-200">Core question</p>
                <p class="mt-1 text-slate-300">
                  Where is the line between helpful automation and loss of understanding, custody, and resilience?
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    {/* FEATURE GRID (WHY PALCHAT) */}
    <section
      id="features"
      class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 pb-12 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 lg:pb-16"
    >
      <div class="mb-8 space-y-3 text-center">
        <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-sky-300">Why Palchat</p>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold tracking-tight text-slate-100 sm:text-2xl">
          A calm place to think about tools
        </h2>
        <p class="mx-auto max-w-2xl text-sm text-slate-300 sm:text-base">
          Instead of selling you another app, Palchat gives you ideas and small, honest tools to see what those apps
          really mean for your work.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-3">
        <article class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/70 p-4 shadow-sm shadow-slate-950/70">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-100 sm:text-base">Short, clear essays</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-xs text-slate-300 sm:text-sm">
            Read one idea at a time. No jargon, no long threads — just plain language you can finish in a few minutes.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/70 p-4 shadow-sm shadow-slate-950/70">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-100 sm:text-base">Tiny tools, not platforms</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-xs text-slate-300 sm:text-sm">
            Use small, focused tools that run in the browser. Helpful enough to guide decisions, simple enough to ignore
            when you are done.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/70 p-4 shadow-sm shadow-slate-950/70">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-100 sm:text-base">No logins required</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-xs text-slate-300 sm:text-sm">
            Open the site, read an idea, try a tool, close the tab. No account, no notifications, no pile of settings.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    {/* SIMPLE WORKFLOW SECTION */}
    <section
      id="workflow"
      class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 pb-12 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 lg:pb-16"
    >
      <div class="mb-6 space-y-3">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold tracking-tight text-slate-100 sm:text-2xl">
          How people use Palchat
        </h2>
        <p class="max-w-2xl text-sm text-slate-300 sm:text-base">
          A simple three–step loop: read, reflect, adjust how you build.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-3">
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/70 p-4">
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-sky-300">01</p>
          <h3 class="mt-1 text-sm font-semibold text-slate-100 sm:text-base">Read one idea</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-xs text-slate-300 sm:text-sm">
            Start with a single short piece, like the dependency trap essay, and sit with it for a minute.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/70 p-4">
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-sky-300">02</p>
          <h3 class="mt-1 text-sm font-semibold text-slate-100 sm:text-base">Look at your own stack</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-xs text-slate-300 sm:text-sm">
            Think about your own tools, subscriptions, and habits. Where are you trading away understanding for speed?
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/70 p-4">
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-sky-300">03</p>
          <h3 class="mt-1 text-sm font-semibold text-slate-100 sm:text-base">Make one small change</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-xs text-slate-300 sm:text-sm">
            Cancel something, move one workflow in–house, or write down the logic you are outsourcing to a black box.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    {/* ESSAY SECTION (MAIN IDEA) */}
    <section
      id="essay"
      class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 pb-16 sm:px-6 lg:px-8"
    >
      <div class="max-w-3xl space-y-4">
        <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-sky-300">Featured idea</p>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-slate-100 sm:text-3xl">
          A dependency trap dressed up as efficiency
        </h2>

        <p class="text-sm text-slate-300 sm:text-base">
          Using AI and SaaS tools instead of people feels smart. You save money, you move faster, and you can serve more
          customers. The $1k vs $40k slide is easy to show in a deck.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-300 sm:text-base">
          But there is a quieter cost that does not show up on any invoice: the slow loss of understanding, custody, and
          resilience inside your own work.
        </p>

        <div class="space-y-3 rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/70 p-4 text-sm text-slate-200 sm:text-base">
          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-slate-100 sm:text-lg">What you actually gain</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-300">
            The gains are real but narrow: lower cost, more speed, more scale. You can take on more clients, handle
            more data, and do it with fewer people. That part of the story is true.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-3 rounded-2xl border border-amber-500/40 bg-slate-900/70 p-4 text-sm text-slate-200 sm:text-base">
          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-amber-200 sm:text-lg">What you quietly lose</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2">
            <li>
              <span class="font-semibold text-slate-100">You lose understanding.</span>{' '}
              <span class="text-slate-300">
                With a human expert, you slowly picked up how the work was done, even if you never learned the field.
                With AI, the work happens in a black box. It is probably correct, but you cannot explain it.
              </span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="font-semibold text-slate-100">You lose custody.</span>{' '}
              <span class="text-slate-300">
                Your data and logic now live inside someone else&apos;s system. You do not own the workflow; you rent
                access to it for as long as you keep paying.
              </span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="font-semibold text-slate-100">You lose resilience.</span>{' '}
              <span class="text-slate-300">
                If a person leaves, you can hire and train a new one. When a tool shuts down, changes terms, or gets
                bought, you can lose the memory of how you run your own business.
              </span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="font-semibold text-slate-100">You lose the relationship as a buffer.</span>{' '}
              <span class="text-slate-300">
                A person might say “something looks off this quarter, want to talk about it?”. A tool just does what you
                ask and stays silent about the rest.
              </span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-3 rounded-2xl border border-sky-500/40 bg-slate-900/70 p-4 text-sm text-slate-200 sm:text-base">
          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-sky-200 sm:text-lg">The deeper problem</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-300">
            One cheap subscription is fine. Ten of them, spread across every part of your work, means you have quietly
            outsourced key pieces of your own competence to ten different companies you do not control.
          </p>
          <p class="text-slate-300">
            The issue is not AI itself. It is the belief that cheaper and easier is always better. Dependency has a
            cost. It just does not show up on the bill.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    {/* FOOTER */}
    <footer class="border-t border-slate-800 bg-slate-950/90">
      <div class="mx-auto flex max-w-6xl flex-col gap-4 px-4 py-6 text-xs text-slate-400 sm:flex-row sm:items-center sm:justify-between sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
          <div class="flex h-7 w-7 items-center justify-center rounded-xl bg-gradient-to-tr from-sky-400 to-purple-500 text-xs font-semibold text-slate-950">
            P
          </div>
          <span>© {new Date().getFullYear()} Palchat. All rights reserved.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4">
          <a href="/about" class="hover:text-sky-300">About</a>
          <a href="/comments" class="hover:text-sky-300">Tech demo</a>
          <a href="mailto:hello@palchat.org" class="hover:text-sky-300">Contact</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </footer>
  </main>
</Layout>
